    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Plain radiographs of the hip\nMay be normal early in disease\nIf high suspicion obtain bone scan or MRI\nImaging findings:\nWidening of cartilage space of affected hip\nSmall size ossific nucleus of femoral head\nSubchondral stress fracture line in femoral head",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "Orthopedic surgery consultation\nNon-weight bearing\nProtection of hip joint (maintain in abduction and internal rotation)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "Generally may be discharged\nShould be done in consultation with orthopedic surgery to ensure appropriate therapy and close follow-up",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
